{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WdSxiK3fbCWnfhSGLhUtia","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story 5-1 is complete. Here is the summary:\n\n**Implemented:** `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` -- the core workflow execution orchestrator that composes all modules from Epics 1-4.\n\n**Key exports:**\n- `executeWorkflow(config: EngineConfig): Promise<EngineResult>` -- sequential flow execution\n- `dispatchTask()` -- single task dispatch with trace IDs, session boundaries, source isolation\n- `loadWorkItems()` -- work item loading from sprint-status.yaml and issues.yaml\n- Interfaces: `EngineConfig`, `EngineResult`, `EngineError`, `WorkItem`\n\n**Tests:** 31 tests in `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts`, all passing. Coverage: 89.91% statements, 81.33% branches, 100% functions, 90.59% lines. Full regression suite: 3955/3955 passing.\n\n**Files changed:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` (new)\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts` (new)\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/5-1-flow-execution-sequential-steps.md` (status: review, tasks checked)\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Boundary test enforcement:** The project has a boundaries.test.ts that requires all `catch` blocks to have `// IGNORE:` comments. Had to add these after the first full-suite run failed. Not a real issue, just a project convention I missed on first pass.\n- **Pre-existing type errors:** `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` has 2 pre-existing TypeScript errors unrelated to this story. Did not fix.\n- **Coverage gaps:** Lines 148-152 (null check on parsed issues YAML) and lines 316-317, 405 (edge cases in flow execution) are uncovered. These are defensive null checks that are hard to trigger through the mock setup since `yaml.parse()` is mocked. Coverage still exceeds the 80% target.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total too